{"id": "EUVD-2022-54509", "enisaUuid": "1d1d00da-2099-3d60-bd09-1f41c1f3364d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nclocksource: hyper-v: unexport __init-annotated hv_init_clocksource()\n\nEXPORT_SYMBOL and __init is a bad combination because the .init.text\nsection is freed up after the initialization. Hence, modules cannot\nuse symbols annotated __init. The access to a freed symbol may end up\nwith kernel panic.\n\nmodpost used to detect it, but it has been broken for a decade.\n\nRecently, I fixed modpost so it started to warn it again, then this\nshowed up in linux-next builds.\n\nThere are two ways to fix it:\n\n  - Remove __init\n  - Remove EXPORT_SYMBOL\n\nI chose the latter for this case because the only in-tree call-site,\narch/x86/kernel/cpu/mshyperv.c is never compiled as modular.\n(CONFIG_HYPERVISOR_GUEST is boolean)", "datePublished": "2025-10-24T21:31:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-24T21:31:09", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cff3a7ce6e81418b6e8bac941779bbf5d342d626", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/db965e2757d95f695e606856418cd84003dd036d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0414eab7c78f3518143d383e448d44fc573ac6d2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/937fcbb55a1e48a6422e87e8f49422c92265f102", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/245b993d8f6c4e25f19191edfbd8080b645e12b1", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49726"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49726"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "01d22cbb-d5c7-381f-b3d1-d4aa3b0cb35f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "16f64433-b49e-388d-aec3-d3769a30af28", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "dd2cb348613b44f9d948b068775e159aad298599 <cff3a7ce6e81418b6e8bac941779bbf5d342d626"}, {"id": "267c3b91-c533-335d-a2c7-e1aa7f4dee1a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.49"}, {"id": "30cb1f6c-f644-3a02-9168-837a176276f3", "product": {"name": "Linu